{
  "title": "Observation.component[] fan-out",
  "notes": "Branch: how `Observation.component[]` fans out. The stage-1 view (`mapspec/views/Observation_component__measurement.view.json`) emits one staging row PER component, carrying the component's own `code.coding.first()` (system+code) and `value[x]`. Stage-2 resolves once in `mapspec/etl/_resolve_observation_component.sql`: each component code goes through `cm.fhir_system_to_omop_vocab` → `vocab.concept` (source) → `Maps to` → standard concept, and `std.domain_id` then ROUTES the component — `Measurement` rows go to `Observation_component__measurement.sql` (and only emit when `component_value_num IS NOT NULL`), `Observation` rows go to `Observation_component__observation.sql`.\n\nThe varying input dimension across variants is: (a) numeric components on a panel parent → `measurement`, vs (b) a coded (`valueCodeableConcept`) component → `observation`.\n\nKey shared facts:\n- The PANEL PARENT is always filtered out: the outer Observation (e.g. BP panel 85354-9) carries no own `value[x]`, so `_resolve_observation.sql`'s value-presence WHERE drops it from `cdm_ours_fhir.measurement`/`observation`. Its clinical content lives entirely in the components, fanned out here. Confirmed live: 0 rows for `measurement_source_value='85354-9'`.\n- `*_type_concept_id` = 32817 ('EHR') — constant in both stage-2 SQLs.\n- date/datetime derive from the PARENT Observation.effective (components inherit it). `::timestamp` keeps WALL-CLOCK (the `+NN:NN` offset is dropped, not converted to UTC).\n- `person_id` ← `subject.getReferenceKey()`, `visit_occurrence_id` ← `encounter.getReferenceKey()`, `provider_id` ← `performer.first()` (NULL when absent).\n- The surrogate PKs are NOT asserted (derived): measurement uses `stringToId(id || '/' || src_code || '|' || std_concept_id)`, observation uses a `/o/` infix so the two families never collide.\n- A component code whose source concept is itself standard self-maps via 'Maps to', so `*_concept_id` == `*_source_concept_id` (true for the BP LOINC codes and for 71802-3).",
